h2. Session Resolution & Infrastructure Configuration

h3. SSM Parameter Store

|| Parameter || Value || Purpose ||
| /prompt2test/ecs/cluster-arn | ECS cluster ARN | Agent reads at session start |
| /prompt2test/ecs/task-definition | Task definition ARN | RunTask call |
| /prompt2test/ecs/subnets | Comma-separated subnet IDs | Task networking |
| /prompt2test/ecs/security-group | Security group ID | Task networking |

h3. DynamoDB Config Table

|| Pattern || pk || sk || Example ||
| Service config | SERVICE#\{team\}#\{env\} | \{service\}#\{key\} | SERVICE#teama#dev / bestbuy#BESTBUY_USA_URL |
| Test accounts | ACCOUNT#\{env\} | \{account_id\} | ACCOUNT#dev / qa-user-1 |

h3. On-Demand Session Flow (9 Steps)

|| Step || What Happens ||
| 1 | User clicks Run Test / Automate |
| 2 | Frontend calls agent {{start_session}} |
| 3 | Agent reads SSM params (cluster, task def, subnets, SG) |
| 4 | Agent calls {{ecs.RunTask()}} — launches Fargate task |
| 5 | Task starts: Chromium + Xvfb + noVNC + Playwright MCP server |
| 6 | Agent waits for MCP endpoint to be healthy (~60s) |
| 7 | Agent returns noVNC URL to frontend |
| 8 | Frontend opens noVNC in new tab, calls {{automate}} or {{replay}} |
| 9 | Agent executes steps via Playwright MCP, streams results |

----

h2. Playwright MCP on ECS Fargate

h3. Task Lifecycle

|| Phase || Duration || What Happens ||
| Startup | ~60s | Pull image, start Xvfb, launch Chromium, start MCP server |
| During test | 30s-5min | Playwright executes steps, noVNC streams to user |
| Teardown | Immediate | Agent calls {{ecs.StopTask()}} — task terminates |

h3. Task Isolation

* 1 task per user session — no sharing
* Each task has its own Xvfb display, Chromium instance, MCP server
* Private IP, port 3000 (MCP) + port 6080 (noVNC)

----

h2. Scaling Model & Cost

h3. Cost by Usage

|| Scenario || Monthly Cost || Notes ||
| *Idle* (no tests) | *~$0.50/mo* | Aurora auto-paused, zero ECS tasks |
| Light (10 tests/day) | ~$15-25/mo | On-demand Fargate + Bedrock tokens |
| Heavy (50+ tests/day) | ~$30-70/mo | Scales linearly with usage |

h3. Key Design Choices

* Zero always-on ECS tasks — spin up per test, stop after
* Aurora auto-pause after 5 min idle — ~$0.50/mo vs $30/mo always-on
* Bedrock pay-per-token — no reserved capacity
* 20+ concurrent test sessions supported (Fargate scaling)

----

h2. End-to-End Request Flow — Timing

h3. Author & Save Flow

|| Step || Time ||
| User pastes scenario | 0s |
| Agent calls get_service_config | ~100ms |
| Claude generates plan | 2-5s |
| User reviews, clicks Generate Final | 2-5s |
| Save to Aurora | 1-2s (warm) / 30-60s (cold, auto-pause resume) |

h3. Execution Flow

|| Step || Time ||
| User clicks Run Test | 0s |
| start_session: ECS RunTask | ~3s |
| Container pull + Chromium startup | ~55s |
| MCP server healthy | ~2s |
| Total cold start | *~60s* |
| Playwright executes 4-5 steps | 15-45s |
| Results saved to Aurora | 1-2s |
| Total execution | *~75-110s* |

